The paper deals with transfer learning in text analytics, specifically sentiment analysis on Twitter data. This falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain, which is typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a regularization technique to address the catastrophic forgetting problem in neural networks, which is a common issue in machine learning and falls under the domain of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for the sentiment analysis task, which is a common technique in NLP and falls under the domain of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). Finally, the paper deals with text classification, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR).
